## IMPORTANT RULES

1. Manager sees only their assigned guest houses via the GH switcher — no other data visible.
2. Admin can assign multiple guest houses to one manager — no limit.
3. Pending Approval rooms are NOT clickable in Room Grid, NOT shown in New Booking room dropdown.
4. Booking submission always goes to Pending first — admin must approve.
5. No partial approval — all rooms in a booking are approved or rejected together.
6. On rejection: all rooms return to Available immediately.
7. On approval: all rooms flip to Booked + confirmation email mock sent to all guests.
8. Rejection always requires a reason — no reason = submit button disabled.
9. Manager CAN cancel a Pending booking themselves (e.g. guest changed mind before admin acted).
10. Cancelling pending booking → all rooms → Available immediately.
11. Check-in and Check-out are per-booking (all guests/rooms at once).
12. Post-checkout cleaning auto-creates a Maintenance ticket — resolved by manager when cleaning is done.
13. Pickup and Drop are recorded per booking — shown on manager dashboard "today" section.
14. Email is SMTP-based but fully mocked in UI — no real API call needed.
15. All reports scoped to selected guest house for manager, all GHs for admin.
16. Expiry timer display should count down live (JS setInterval) from pending_expires_at.
17. When timer hits 0: booking → Rejected (reason: "Auto-rejected: approval window expired"), rooms → Available, show toast to manager.

